article.headline: Jackson State 58, Stephen F. Austin 54
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Hilton Tompkins hit the go-ahead jumper with 24 seconds left as Jackson State ended Stephen F. Austin's 31-game home winning streak with a 58-54 win. Tompkins hit a 16-foot jumper that put Jackson State (2-7) on top 56-54. Stephen F. Austin (2-5) had the second-longest winning streak in the country behind Wisconsin, whose home streak is at 32 games. Taylor Moore scored 17 points for the Lumberjacks and Anthony Paez had 11 points and eight rebounds. Jackson State's Antonio Williams-Parker had 11 points and Ernest Hassell had 10.
